sections.text:
The inclusion criteria were:
1. Presenting to the hospital with suspected TBI (isolated) occurring no more than 6 h before arrival at the hospital (with the first sampling time occurring at a maximum of 6 h after the injury); 2. GCS ranging from 13 to 15 (mild TBI or concussion);
3. Patient conscious at the time of recruitment; 4. Signed written informed consent form, in Finnish or Swedish, signed by the par-
ent/legal guardian and also by the study subject if he/she was considered capable of understanding the study measures;
5. Age 0–17 years (male or female).
